You missed just single thing here. i18n works before data() in vue component. So this.resource won’t work.

To solve it, you can use it like below:

    export default {
      name: &quot;App&quot;,
      data() {
        return {
          resource: new TestClass()
        };
      },
      i18n: {
        messages: {
          en: {
            local: &quot;Local message in English&quot;
          },
          nl: {
            local: &quot;Lokaal bericht in het Nederlands&quot;
          }
        },
        sharedMessages: new TestClass().i18n,
      }
    };

If you want to go on with data, you can use mergeLocaleMessage.

    import i18n from &#39;@/i18n.js&#39;; //your plugin path.
    i18n.mergeLocaleMessage(i18n.locale, this.resource.i18n[i18n.locale]);

